The Public Accounts Committee of the House of Representatives yesterday summoned four ministers to appear before it within seven days. They are to respond to audit queries from the office of the Auditor General of the Federation (OAGF) between 2016 and 2019. The ministers are: Babatunde Raji Fashola (Works and Housing), Dr. Osagie Ehanire (Health), Rauf Aregbesola (Interior) and Ali Isa Pantami (Communication and Digital Economy).   Taraba Senator Lau is Deputy Minority Leader     Alleged N2.9b fraud: Court orders EFCC to stop all actions…     Igboho a prisoner of conscience, says lawyer   Committee Chairman Oluwole Oke, who issued the ultimatum during the committee’s seating, said permanent secretaries and directors of finance in the listed ministries are also to appear alongside the ministers. - Advertisement - Oke said the ultimatum became necessary following the alleged refusal of the ministers to honour several invitations extended to them by the committee. The Public Account Committee is one of the constitutional committees of the House and is statutorily mandated to examine reports from the OAGF.